Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Dark ashy soil with flue tiles in the hypocaust room

Locus 8 is a dumping layer in the "hypocaust room" filled with flues tiles, pottery and marble. The locus covers the room and is made up of loose, porous silt-soil which does ball. The Munsell color of the soil in this locus is 7.5 YR 3/2, Dark Brown. There are a huge amount of inclusions in this locus of including ash, pottery and burnt residue. This dumping seems to be a later development than the primary use of the room as there is a cleaner dirt layer, locus 9, between it and the floor of the room.
